# N-Queens Problem using Python

## Project Description

This project is an implementation of the N-Queens Problem using Python, developed as part of the Codveda Python Development Internship.

The N-Queens Problem is a classic backtracking algorithm challenge where N queens must be placed on an N×N chessboard so that no two queens attack each other. The application finds and displays valid arrangements of queens on the chessboard while following all constraints.

## Features

- Solves the N-Queens problem using Backtracking
- Finds valid queen placements on the chessboard
- Displays solutions in a readable board format
- Supports different board sizes (N)
- Efficient conflict checking for queen positions
- Simple command-line interface
- Basic error handling for invalid inputs

## Technologies Used

- Python
- Backtracking Algorithm
- Functions and Loops
- Lists and Arrays
- Command-Line Interface (CLI)

